	"keywords": "Responsive Design, CSS",
	"description": "I ran a poll on Twitter awhile ago, and the results surprised me.\n\nNot only did I expect the results to be the other way around, I thought that\nmobile-first would get at least 80% of the vote.\n\nDesktop-first wins with more than 61% of the vote!In the replies, some people\nexplained why they write desktop-first. The general themes of those reasons: \n\n * That&#x27;s all the designer supplied\n * That&#x27;s how their team functioned\n * They learned CSS writing it Desktop only, so this seemed like the natural\n",
	"headline": "How to Take the Right Approach to Responsive Web Design",
